                            <comment id="232789" author="gerrit" created="Thu, 30 Aug 2018 06:24:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Andreas Dilger (adilger@whamcloud.com) merged in patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/33075/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/33075/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-412&quot; title=&quot;About Max OSTs Size. 256TB vs 256TiB&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LUDOC-412&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUDOC-412&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; misc: Update byte prefixes to use IEC&lt;br/&gt;
Project: doc/manual&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: &lt;br/&gt;
Commit: 1f935d0231c9f14bbe5e07c87a31bcacd0492ae6&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="232604" author="adilger" created="Sun, 26 Aug 2018 03:50:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There is not really an upper size limit for ZFS, but this is the recommended maximum for management and performance reasons. The ZFS filesystems could be larger if there is not a need for high performance, just capacity, but we have never tested such large filesystems ourselves, nor do we know of any sites using larger ZFS filesystems. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="232590" author="gerrit" created="Fri, 24 Aug 2018 21:08:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Joseph Gmitter (jgmitter@whamcloud.com) uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/33075&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/33075&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-412&quot; title=&quot;About Max OSTs Size. 256TB vs 256TiB&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LUDOC-412&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUDOC-412&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; misc: Update byte prefixes to use IEC&lt;br/&gt;
Project: doc/manual&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: 1&lt;br/&gt;
Commit: 76f3092a1f503be523c409edca6c9d51d7381c32&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="232588" author="jgmitter" created="Fri, 24 Aug 2018 20:51:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Moved the ticket to an LUDOC for correcting the manual.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="232354" author="isbckorea" created="Tue, 21 Aug 2018 12:56:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks. That means Binary. then actual limit is below &#160;right?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;128TiB =&#160;140.737TB , Max Ldiskfs size limit&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;256TiB =&#160;281.475TB , Max ZFS size limit&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="232353" author="adilger" created="Tue, 21 Aug 2018 12:53:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It is binary size limits, so TiB. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="232347" author="jinho40" created="Tue, 21 Aug 2018 06:55:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Additional questions.&lt;br/&gt;
If Lustre is ldiskfs, Is it 128TB per OST?&#160; Is 128 TiB correct?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
